title: Chinese ship's anchor caused damage to Baltic gas pipeline, Finland suggests
description: A Chinese container ship's dislodged anchor caused damage to a Baltic Sea gas pipeline between Finland and Estonia, Finnish police believe.

title: Off-duty pilot 'who tried to shut down plane's engines had tried magic mushrooms for first time'
description: An off-duty pilot who allegedly tried to shut down a plane's engines during a flight told police after his arrest he had taken psychedelic mushrooms for the first time, prosecutors say.

title: Man jailed for sending over 200 abusive messages to father of school shooting victim
description: A property manager has been sentenced to a year in prison for sending more than 200 abusive messages to the father of a teenage girl who died in a Florida mass shooting.

title: Shamima Begum's British citizenship removal was 'unlawful', Court of Appeal hears
description: The decision to remove Shamima Begum's British citizenship was "unlawful", a court has heard, as her latest appeal against the decision begins.

title: K-pop band accidentally wear old Glasgow Rangers shirts to perform Texas show
description: It's been a tried and tested tactic of musicians for decades - don a garment representing a beloved sporting team in the area where you are performing.

title: Israeli military drops leaflets in Gaza offering rewards and protection for information on hostages
description: The Israeli military has been dropping leaflets in Gaza asking Palestinians to reveal information on hostages' whereabouts.

title: More than 500 people 'being held hostage' in gold mine
description: At least 500 workers are being held down a South African gold mine by a rival union, according to the head of the site.

title: Ancient rock carvings of human faces revealed by Amazon River drought
description: Ancient human faces carved into stone around 2,000 years ago have been revealed by a historic drought along the Amazon River.

title: Putin 'fine',  Kremlin says amid more reports of illness - and comments on body double rumours
description: The Kremlin has dismissed fresh speculation that Russian President Vladimir Putin is ill and called rumours that he uses a body double an "absurd hoax".

title: Gangsters torch at least 35 buses after 'man of war' crime boss killed by police
description: Gangsters have reportedly set at least 35 buses on fire in Rio de Janeiro after a crime boss known as "man of war" was killed by police in an operation.

title: Revealed: The staggering amount of electricity that Bitcoin uses
description: Bitcoin mining consumes more electricity than most countries, according to a new report on its damaging environmental impact.

title: IDF ground assault delay to avoid Hamas 'deadly trap' in Gaza
description: Israel is taking its time before launching a ground invasion into Gaza as troops would have "fallen into a deadly trap" set by Hamas had they entered too quickly, a top Israeli diplomat has said.

title: Dwayne Johnson 'belly laughs' after controversial waxwork unveiled
description: A museum has changed the skin tone of its Dwayne Johnson wax statue after it was criticised for being too white.

title: China dismisses defence minister who has been missing for two months
description: China's defence minister, who has been missing from public life for nearly two months, has been removed from his post, according to state media.

title: 'Life stopped': British-based families of Hamas attack victims speak of grief
description: The British-based families of people killed or taken hostage in Hamas's 7 October attack on Israel have spoken of their grief.

title: Freed hostage says Hamas were 'prepared' for kidnappings and IDF did not take warnings 'seriously'
description: Hamas were "really prepared" for kidnapping Israeli citizens and holding them captive, a hostage freed by the militants had told the press in Tel Aviv.

title: 'Armed and dangerous' man on the run after wife found dead
description: An "armed and dangerous" man is on the run in Massachusetts after his wife was found dead.

title: Beer brand's share price falls after man filmed urinating in factory vat
description: A man was seen urinating into a vat at a Tsingtao beer factory, with the brand now opening a probe into the incident.

title: Hamas has six British hostages, govt fears
description: Six British nationals are suspected to be among those being held hostage by Hamas, a minister has told Sky News.

title: British cargo ship sinks off coast of Germany - several missing after collision
description: A British cargo ship has reportedly sunk off the coast of Germany following a collision, and several people are missing.

title: Family's joy at release of two more hostages as British daughter flies to Israel
description: Hamas has released two more hostages, with the British daughter of one of the women flying to Israel and saying she's relieved beyond words.

title: 10 revelations from Britney Spears's book
description: Almost two years after the end of her conservatorship, Britney Spears is telling her story in her own words with the release of her memoir The Woman In Me.
